<task id="047" project="spaarke-ai-platform-chat-routing-redesign-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Populate DispatchResult.NodeDestination + WidgetType in PlaybookDispatcher</title>
    <phase>3: WP3 Destination Metadata Wiring</phase>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-hours>3</estimated-hours>
    <dependencies>027</dependencies>
    <blocks>048,049,054</blocks>
    <tags>bff-api, services, ADR-013, ADR-029</tags>
    <rigor-hint>FULL</rigor-hint>
    <rigor-reason>Tags include 'bff-api'; modifies hot-path dispatcher service `.cs` file — FULL per Step 0.5</rigor-reason>
    <parallel-group>3-A</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    In `PlaybookDispatcher` (the chat-routing service that returns `DispatchResult`), after a playbook matches, load its primary AI/DeliverOutput node and call `NodeRoutingConfig.Parse(node.ConfigJson)`. Populate `DispatchResult.NodeDestination` and `DispatchResult.WidgetType` from the parsed config. Backward compat: null/empty `sprk_configjson` falls back to `Destination = Chat`, `WidgetType = null` (per FR-14f). Implements spec FR-14c.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in `PlaybookDispatcher` + `NodeRoutingConfig.Parse` + Dataverse playbook node loading.</role>

  <goal>
    `PlaybookDispatcher.DispatchAsync` returns `DispatchResult` with populated `NodeDestination` + `WidgetType` reflecting the matched playbook's primary node's `sprk_configjson`. Integration test dispatching `summarize-document-for-workspace` returns `{ NodeDestination: Workspace, WidgetType: "structured-output-stream" }`. Integration test dispatching a playbook with null `sprk_configjson` returns `{ NodeDestination: Chat }`.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-14c + design §1.3 (WP3 step 3). The dispatcher already returns `DispatchResult`; tasks 045 (Both enum) and 046 (record extension) made this possible. Now we wire it. The "primary AI/DeliverOutput node" is the node that triggers `PlaybookOutputHandler` — typically the last node in the playbook graph.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/PlaybookDispatcher.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/NodeRoutingConfig.cs</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Models/Ai/Chat/DispatchResult.cs</file>
      <file>tests/integration/Sprk.Bff.Api.IntegrationTests/Services/Ai/Chat/</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">Service lives in `Services/Ai/Chat/`; AI-internal.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-014">Cached playbook lookup respected — do not re-fetch on warm cache hits.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">Per-task BFF publish-size measurement.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-14c acceptance: dispatching `summarize-document-for-workspace` returns Workspace + structured-output-stream.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-14f acceptance: null `sprk_configjson` returns Chat default.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Preserve R6 FR-26 convergence invariant (chat-summarize playbook dispatch unchanged in behavior).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">CLAUDE.md §10 test obligation — add integration tests for populated dispatch.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
